{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/no-frills-kubernetes-dashboard/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"9dd63b55-2582-5e2b-bdbe-e6ae7b046f6b","html":"<blockquote>\n<p>No frills is an ongoing series that doesn‚Äôt give the background or really anything other than ‚Äúhere‚Äôs how to do that thing you are trying to do‚Äù. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Here‚Äôs how to connect to a Kubernetes cluster with authentication in just a few steps. Check out the documentation <a href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/access-application-cluster/web-ui-dashboard/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">here</a> for some more background.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I use powershell for running these on a windows machine</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"connect-to-kubernetes-cluster\"><a href=\"#connect-to-kubernetes-cluster\" aria-label=\"connect to kubernetes cluster permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Connect to kubernetes cluster</h3>\n<p>Make sure you have the kubernetes cluster as your current context with</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ps1\"><pre class=\"language-ps1\"><code class=\"language-ps1\">kubectl config current-context</code></pre></div>\n<p>to view your context, and</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ps1\"><pre class=\"language-ps1\"><code class=\"language-ps1\">kubectl config use-context &lt;cluster-name&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>to change your current context.</p>\n<h3 id=\"make-sure-the-dashboard-is-deployed\"><a href=\"#make-sure-the-dashboard-is-deployed\" aria-label=\"make sure the dashboard is deployed permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Make sure the dashboard is deployed</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ps1\"><pre class=\"language-ps1\"><code class=\"language-ps1\">kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes/dashboard/v2.0.0/aio/deploy/recommended.yaml</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"run-the-dashboard\"><a href=\"#run-the-dashboard\" aria-label=\"run the dashboard permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Run the dashboard</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ps1\"><pre class=\"language-ps1\"><code class=\"language-ps1\">kubectl proxy</code></pre></div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Dashboard should now be available at <a href=\"http://localhost:8001/api/v1/namespaces/kubernetes-dashboard/services/https:kubernetes-dashboard:/proxy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">http://localhost:8001/api/v1/namespaces/kubernetes-dashboard/services/https:kubernetes-dashboard:/proxy</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"login-for-azure-kubernetes-service-aks\"><a href=\"#login-for-azure-kubernetes-service-aks\" aria-label=\"login for azure kubernetes service aks permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Login (for Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS))</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ps1\"><pre class=\"language-ps1\"><code class=\"language-ps1\">az aks get-credentials -a --resource-group &lt;RG_NAME&gt; --name &lt;CLUSTER_NAME&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>You only have to do this if you haven‚Äôt done it before for this cluster (or its erroring).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Now, in the login screen select Kubeconfig and use the file from <code class=\"language-text\">%USERPROFILE%\\.kube\\config</code>.</p>\n<p>üéâ Sign in, and you should be good to go! üéâ</p>\n<p>I hope this guide was useful and helps you solve more problems!</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/no-frills-kubernetes-dashboard/","tagSlugs":["/tag/no-frills/","/tag/kubernetes/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-03-01T12:00:00.000Z","description":"A no-frills topic on how to add and connect to a kubernetes dashboard (with authentication).","tags":["No frills","Kubernetes"],"title":"No Frills: Kubernetes Dashboard","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/no-frills-kubernetes-dashboard/"}}}